#
# @(#)README.make_release_packages	1.1 94/05/23
#
Make_release_packages creates and fills a package staging area.

This script should be run from the base of the build tree.  It takes
one parameter: the name of the directory to put the packages in.

Example:
	%cd /win/ow
	%./proto-tool-Obj-$ARCH-svr4/make_release_packages OL-3.4

Normally most of the bin directory is copied and then stripped.
This can be prevented by using the `--nostrip' option.

Example:
	%cd /win/ow
	%./proto-tool-Obj-$ARCH-svr4/make_release_packages OL-3.4 --nostrip
